  • Constructor Details

    • CcddTableTreeHandler

      CcddTableTreeHandler(CcddMain ccddMain, CcddGroupHandler groupHandler, CcddConstants.TableTreeType treeType, boolean getDescriptions, boolean sortByName, boolean showGroupFilter, boolean showTypeFilter, boolean addHiddenCheckbox, String rateName, String rateFilter, List<String> excludedVariables, boolean isSilent, String prototypeNodeName, String instanceNodeName, boolean skipMemberTables, boolean buildGroupTree, boolean buildTypeTree, Component parent)
      Table tree handler class constructor
      Parameters:
      ccddMain - Main class
      groupHandler - Group handler
      treeType - Table tree type (TableTreeType)
      getDescriptions - True if the node descriptions are to be added as tool tips
      sortByName - True to sort the child structures by variable name; false to show in the order defined in the structure
      showGroupFilter - True to display the group filter check box
      showTypeFilter - True to display the type filter check box
      addHiddenCheckbox - True to add a hidden check box under the filter check boxes for alignment purposes
      rateName - Data stream rate column name used to filter the table tree for variables with rates
      rateFilter - Data rate used to filter the table tree for variables with rates
      excludedVariables - List of node paths to be excluded from the table; null or empty list if no exclusions
      isSilent - True if any errors when building the tree are not annunciated via a warning dialog
      prototypeNodeName - Name of the prototype node; null to set the node to which the prototype node would normally belong as the prototype node
      instanceNodeName - Name of the instance node; null to set node to which the instance node would normally belong as the instance node
      skipMemberTables - Do not include the members of any root tables
      buildGroupTree - True to build the group tree used by the TableTreeHandler instantiated by CcddMain
      buildTypeTree - True to build the type tree used by the TableTreeHandler instantiated by CcddMain
      parent - GUI component over which to center any error dialog

    • CcddTableTreeHandler

      CcddTableTreeHandler(CcddMain ccddMain, CcddGroupHandler groupHandler, CcddConstants.TableTreeType treeType, boolean showGroupFilter, boolean addHiddenCheckbox, boolean skipMemberTables, Component parent)
      Table tree handler class constructor
      Parameters:
      ccddMain - Main class
      groupHandler - Group handler
      treeType - Table tree type (TableTreeType)
      showGroupFilter - True to display the group filter check box
      addHiddenCheckbox - True to add a hidden check box under the filter check boxes for alignment purposes
      skipMemberTables - True to skip member tables
      parent - GUI component over which to center any error dialog

      Starting with the specified node, traverse down its branch and flag as invalid any node where the name doesn't match one in the supplied list of tables.       node - Node to test for validity
      Returns:

    • getSelectedTablesWithoutChildren

      protected List<String> getSelectedTablesWithoutChildren()
      Get a list of the tables (with their paths) represented by the selected nodes. Eliminate any tables from the list that are children of another selected table. If a header node (i.e., a non-table node one level above a table node, such as a group or type node) is selected then its descendants are checked, recursively, until the level containing tables is found; these tables are added to the list. If a selected node isn't a header node then ignore the node if it has a selected ancestor node. HTML tags are removed from the returned table path+names
      Returns:
      List containing the table path+names of the selected node(s) (minus any children of the selected nodes) with any HTML tags removed
